metadata.name: Room #1 : Transi in the mountains
metadata.description:
A "transi", in the funerary art of the late Middle Ages and the Renaissance, is a sculpture representing a dead person. The term "transi", from the verb "transir", etymologically means "to go, to pass beyond", that is to say, to die, in the same way as the most modern deceased.

[1/1] | 4000px x 4000px
